São Paulo. Through the idea of the “cluster,” Merkel traces the intertwined networks of Claude Lévi-Strauss, Fernand Braudel, Roger Bastide, and Pierre Monbeig as they overlapped at USP and engaged with Brazilian scholars such as Mário de Andrade, Gilberto Freyre, and Caio Prado Jr. Through this collective intellectual biography of Brazilian and French social sciences, Terms of Exchange reveals connections that shed new light on the Annales school, structuralism, and racial democracy, even as it prompts us to revisit established thinking on the process of knowledge formation through fieldwork and intellectual exchange. At a time when canons are being rewritten, this book reframes the history of modern social scientific thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aIntellectualszBrazilzSão Paulo. 0aSocial scienceszBrazilzSão PauloxHistory. 0aSocial scienceszFrancexHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  abrazil, brazilian society, intellectuals, intellectualism, french social sciences, biography, biographical narratives, intellectual thought, university of sao paulo, pierre monbeig, roger bastide, fernand braudel, claude levi-strauss, caio prado jr, gilberto freyre, mario de andrade, structuralism, racial democracy, race, democratic government, knowledge formation, fieldwork, reconstruction, metissage, decolonization, colonialism, power dynamics, academics, academia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package: